rComments: Arthur was an excellent professor. He always explained concepts clearly, and was very friendly and understanding. The math in this course was way below his level of knowledge, but he was able to teach it in a comprehensible manner. Hope I'll have him again in the future!

You don't often get the chance to learn multivariable calculus from a first class world-renowned Mathematician. He usually teaches courses that though hard for a mere student, are far below his level of expertise. You can unlock his brain if you ask him tempting questions.
